<p>When it comes to measuring speed or velocity though, ã§ cannot be omitted. To express speed in a kilometers per hour format, the Japanese is æ™‚é€Ÿã€œã‚­ãƒ­<strong>ã§</strong>. If you want, you can swap this out for miles too, and say æ™‚é€Ÿã€œãƒã‚¤ãƒ«<strong>ã§</strong>. In either case, the ã§ is a required element. Let's check out this phrase is an example sentence:</p>

